# Cross-platform line-ending normalization — SIGN + MANAGEX monorepo.
#
# Policy: every text file is stored as LF in the repository AND checked out as
# LF, regardless of the contributor's OS. This prevents the CRLF-on-Linux
# failures documented in lessons.md #15 (a CRLF `docker-entrypoint.sh` crashed
# the backend container with `/usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory`)
# and the CRLF warnings Windows contributors see on commit.

# Default: auto-detect text vs binary; for text, normalize to LF in the repo
# and force LF in the working tree on every platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Shell scripts MUST be LF ---
# CRLF here breaks the Linux Docker entrypoint (lessons.md #15). Forced as text
# so detection can never misclassify them.
*.sh text eol=lf

# --- Binary files: never normalize line endings, never diff as text ---
# Images
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.ico  binary
# Documents
*.pdf  binary
# Office Open XML (zip-based) documents
*.docx binary
*.xlsx binary
*.pptx binary
# Fonts
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
# Archives
*.zip binary
*.gz  binary
